						<div class="postbody">We're talking about two different, but related, issues here.  I'm referring to synchronization in the context of this particular method of adjusting audio rate.  In other words, how to (re-)determine the correct audio playback rate following a desync event.  The issue you're referring to is applicable to all emulators, and I agree that window size/move events should be properly handled (I simply pause emulation and stop audio playback while sizing/moving).</div>

					
